works.description: At the International Furniture Fair in Milan, Italy, Fiat showcased its new Fiat 500 Design Collection, which pays a tribute to the brand’s heritage and the original Fiat 500. Designed in partnership with interior design firm Meritalia and Fiat chairman’s brother Lapo Elkann, the collection includes a sofa (Panorama), a table (Picnic) and a console (Cincin), all based on the 1957 Fiat 500. All three units carry a plate that says…Lapo and Meritalia pay tribute to the Fiat 500.
